form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: Notice of Denial for Status as a Temporary Resident, I-692

full_text: Screened by NARA, 7/13/2023 U.S. Department of J ice Notice of nial for Status Immigration and Naturalization Service as a Temporary Resident Date: OCT 17 1988 U.S. Department of Justice Immigration & Naturalization Service Regional Processing Center P.O. Box 590 Williston, VT 05495 QDE/Volag No: File No: A91 318 117 MEDARDA VALERIO LAMBERT 2217 8TH AVE 3J NEW YORK, NY 10026 Your application for Temporary Residence has been denied. The reason (s) for the denial are stated below: SEE ATTACHMENT You may appeal this decision to the Administrative Appeals Unit by completing the enclosed Form I-694, (NOTICE OF APPEAL), in triplicate, and filing it with this office together with a $50.00 fee in the form of a money order, cashier's check, or bank draft. Your NOTICE OF APPEAL must be filed within 30 days of this notice. Additional evidence, a brief, or other written statement in support of your appeal may be submitted with the NOTICE OF APPEAL. If no appeal is filed within the time allowed, this decision is final. If a timely appeal is not submitted, all employment authorization previously granted by this Service will be automatically revoked. FEE WILL ONLY BE ACCEPTED IN THE FORM OF A MONEY ORDER, CASHIER'S CHECK, OR BANK DRAFT. NO PERSONAL CHECKS WILL BE ACCEPTED. Enclosure: Sincerely, Savid W. wolfe David W. Wolfe Director Regional Processing Facility Form I-692
